        <abstract> 
<p>Agrees that CD should write to Lord Derby to say that a bill on animal experimentation was being prepared and that the government should not comment at this stage. [See <hi rend="doubleUnderline">9933</hi>.] Ridicules the idea of using inspectors. Distinguishes between dissection and vivisection.</p> 
        </abstract>
